 <body>
  <p>The Creative Designer allows you to easily define the structure of your email. By adding and moving structural elements with simple drag &amp; drop actions, you can design the shape of your email within seconds.</p> 
  <ol>
   <li><p>Open an existing content or create a new email content.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Access the <strong>Structure components</strong> by selecting the <strong>+</strong> icon on the left.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Drag and drop the structure components you need to shape your email.</p> <p>A blue line materializes the exact location of the structure components before you drop it. You can drop it above, between or below any other component, but not inside.</p> 
    <note>
     <p> Once placed in the email, you cannot move nor remove your components unless there is already a content/fragment placed inside. </p> 
    </note></li>
  </ol>
  <p>Once the structure is defined, you are able to add content fragments and components to your email, as explained in <a href="../../designing/using/adding-fragments-and-content-components.md">this section</a>.</p> 
